# Improvement Pill → Eval Dataset

## Data Sources

- **Ranking** (by view_count): `source/data.json` → `ImprovementPill.videos[]`
- **Scripts** (formatted [HOOK]/[BODY]/[CLOSE]): `generation/references/improvementpill/{videoId}.md`
- **Output**: `eval-ui/public/eval-dataset.json`

## Adding Videos

Run the script (from project root):

```bash
python3 generation/scripts/eval/add_improvementpill_to_eval.py
```

The script adds videos at ranks 11–25 by default. It reads the ranking from `source/data.json`, extracts scripts from the `.md` files, and appends new entries to `eval-dataset.json` (skips already-present IDs).

## Entry Structure

Each eval entry has:
- `nuggetId`: `improvement-pill-{videoId}`
- `rawContent`: transcript from `source/data.json`
- `script.default`: content from `generation/references/improvementpill/{videoId}.md` (text between triple-backtick fences)
- `sourceRef`: `Improvement Pill · https://www.youtube.com/watch?v={videoId}`
- `sourceType`: `youtube` (used by validate_judges for holdout expected labels; backfilled on existing entries when script runs)

## Adding More Ranks

To add ranks 26–40 (or another range), edit `add_improvementpill_to_eval.py`: change the slice from `videos[10:25]` to the desired range (e.g. `videos[25:40]`).
